quote: Who could have anticipated that Marvel Studios and Disney would release a three-hour extravaganza whose exquisite character-focused scenes outshine the FX-driven action?
critic.name: Brian Eggert
publication.name: Deep Focus Review

quote: Eleven years of Universe building, and this is the crescendo. It really pays off, I've never seen anything quite like it.
critic.name: James Luxford
publication.name: BBC.com

quote: Avengers: Endgame broke me, put me back together, and decided to cut me again in one of the most impactful cinematic experiences of all time.
critic.name: David Gonzalez
publication.name: Reel Talk Inc.

quote: For me, it didn't fulfill the promise of Infinity War, but it did fulfill the promise of the previous twenty movies.
critic.name: Lonita Cook
publication.name: KCTV5 News at 9

quote: I'm just grateful to have the privilege to watch this along with the rest of the world. It's not perfect, but it has been one hell of a ride.
critic.name: Nicholas Oon
publication.name: Maximum Hype (YouTube)

quote: Here's the other really neat thing about Endgame: it made me think of priorities in life and what or who is worth sacrificing for, especially loved ones...
critic.name: Hosea Rupprecht
publication.name: Pauline Center for Media Studies

quote: The true superteam event releases marked something slightly different and spectacular...End Game over the original Guardians by a hair...
critic.name: Nathan Mattise
publication.name: Ars Technica

quote: This goes beyond the usual scale.
critic.name: Robin Holabird
publication.name: KUNR (Reno, NV)

quote: A film that somehow manages to be as epic as fans hope and as dramatic as the MCU deserves.
critic.name: Rick Marshall
publication.name: Digital Trends

quote: Films don't come any huger than this: the closing chapter to an 11-year saga in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, told across some 22 movies. And by the end of its three-hour runtime, there will definitely be tears.
critic.name: Nick Levine
publication.name: NME

quote: There really is very little that could be improved about Endgame. There's certainly no more that could be thrown at it.
critic.name: Olly Richards
publication.name: NME

quote: So much of the art form is about storytelling, and bringing so many side stories and characters to a satisfying conclusion is tough, and the film blended a (rather) unpredictable plot with emotional character beats deftly...
critic.name: Luiz Oliveira
publication.name: Battleship Pretension

quote: Avengers: Endgame is everything Marvel fans could want and more. It will be interesting to see how the MCU moves into the future after the events in the film, but woe be upon anyone who doubts their ability to adapt and succeed mightily.
critic.name: Alex Bentley
publication.name: CultureMap

quote: I found Avengers: Endgame wonderfully satisfying.
critic.name: Fletcher Powell
publication.name: KMUW - Wichita Public Radio

quote: There are [Marvel] movies that have been just as entertaining and a lot smarter than this one.
critic.name: Ian Simmons
publication.name: Kicking the Seat

quote: Feels like the end of the old cycle, the beginning of a reset. Old favourites gone, passing the mantle to others before they go. We even see a poster that reads, "Where do we go, now that they're all gone?"
critic.name: Richard Crouse
publication.name: Richard Crouse

quote: The MCU is the ultimate long game, and Endgame feels like its glorious final lap.
critic.name: Jeffrey Zhang
publication.name: Strange Harbors

quote: Terms like masterpiece and game-changer are often thrown around a bit hastily, but not on this occasion.
critic.name: Mark Cassidy
publication.name: ComicBookMovie.com

quote: The fight scenes, while chaotic and intermittently exhilarating, are unable to avoid repetition; such is the nature of invincible entities dueling other invincible entities.
critic.name: Mike Massie
publication.name: Gone With The Twins

quote: "Avengers: Endgame" was a wonderful surprise, filling almost every minute (all 181 of them) with excitement, drama, humor, and visually interesting and entertaining intrigue.
critic.name: Charles Koplinski
publication.name: Reel Talk with Chuck and Pam

quote: What The Russo Brothers did here is take high expectations and blow them out of the water with an emotionally thrilling finale. Get ready to be moved!
critic.name: Dan Buffa
publication.name: KSDK News (St. Louis)

quote: The only thing that I know for sure has ended with the Marvel Cinematic Universe is my patience.
critic.name: Richard Propes
publication.name: TheIndependentCritic.com

quote: Endgame is nothing short of a deserved send-off to the Infinity Saga, stamping an impressive mark on the cultural psyche. It has been one hell of a ride.
critic.name: Kelechi Ehenulo
publication.name: Confessions From A Geek Mind

quote: Part of the journey is the end, and this one is perfect for certain characters. An unprecedented movie in film history, and a very difficult feat to repeat. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Victor Pineyro
publication.name: Seventh Art Studio

quote: Neither the best nor the worst of times in the franchise, it's a bit like a sugar rush. Endgame delivers both epics highs and a following crash that leaves you feeling oddly empty.
critic.name: Stephen A. Russell
publication.name: The New Daily (Australia)

quote: It's that the movie itself is overblown and half-baked, and without the audience, it's something of a glorified in-joke.
critic.name: Matt Cipolla
publication.name: Film Monthly

quote: If Infinity War wanted to blow you away, Endgame wants to punch you in the gut and leave you a speechless, quivering wreck.
critic.name: James Hanton
publication.name: Outtake Mag

quote: The 22nd installment is a fittingly epic, three-hour finale that packs all of the fan service you could ever want, laced with somber tones and emotional payoffs that will cause even the genre's biggest detractors to shed a tear.
critic.name: Jason Fraley
publication.name: WTOP (Washington, D.C.)

quote: It's one of the funniest movies of the 20-plus in the franchise, but it's also the one that made me the most emotional. But more than anything, it left me satisfied and thrilled that I kept watching them through the years.
critic.name: Steven Prokopy
publication.name: Third Coast Review

quote: For fans of the most successful franchise in movie history, Avengers: Endgame delivers the world - and more.
critic.name: Saibal Chatterjee
publication.name: NDTV

quote: Epic and spectacular, an emotional rollercoaster that none of us will ever forget.
critic.name: Zehra Phelan
publication.name: Flavourmag

quote: Avengers: Endgame is the most 'superhero movie' superhero movie ever made.
critic.name: Allen Almachar
publication.name: The MacGuffin

quote: The film is almost three hours long; long enough to tie up loose ends, as well as give foundation to a new generation of Avengers. When all is said and done, this was the hardest goodbye in the Marvel Universe.
critic.name: Nabila Hatimy
publication.name: The Star (Kenya)

quote: A genuine, spectacular, and moving love letter from the Marvel family, the world of comics and the Russo brothers to modern pop culture. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Ricardo Gallegos
publication.name: Pólvora

quote: A good movie with a breathtaking third act for any comic book fan.
critic.name: Doug Walker
publication.name: Channel Awesome

quote: While there are a few ho-hum moments, there are equally stunning, stirring, triumphant ones where it's damn near impossible not to cheer.
critic.name: Brent McKnight
publication.name: The Last Thing I See

quote: Overall, Endgame was a satisfying high-stakes adventure that was at times even unpredictable.
critic.name: Nikki Francisco
publication.name: Cosmopolitan (Philippines)

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a masterfully triumphant epic. It's a superhero film on a scope and scale the likes of which we've never seen.
critic.name: Damond Fudge
publication.name: KCCI (Des Moines, IA)

quote: It puts my heart racing like a locomotive in some of the most spectacular sequences I have seen in this cinematic universe that, apparently, closes a cycle to open a new one. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Yasser Medina
publication.name: Cinemaficionados

quote: The whole thing is as sentimental as it is exhilarating, but any cheesiness feels well-earned.
critic.name: Alex Hudson
publication.name: Exclaim!

quote: All told, Endgame is a highly satisfying celebration of 10 years of the MCU, and a great bookend to the first three phases.
critic.name: Dan Tabor
publication.name: Phawker

quote: It was exactly what it needed to be and nothing more.
critic.name: Avaryl Halley
publication.name: Movie Bitches

quote: It was good.
critic.name: Andrew Galdi
publication.name: Movie Bitches

quote: I wouldn't have believed the breezy and tongue-in-cheek Avengers Assemble would evolve into such an odiously self-important endeavour a mere seven years later.
critic.name: PJ Nabarro
publication.name: Patrick Nabarro

quote: As fun as the movie is, there's an undeniable hollowness at its core induced by its unwillingness to follow through on certain ideas and symbols.
critic.name: Dan Schindel
publication.name: Hyperallergic

quote: podcast review
critic.name: Julian Lytle
publication.name: Ignorant Bliss

quote: I'm not naïve enough to suppose that anything I can say here is likely to change anyone's plans about going or not going, so I'll simply say that I enjoyed this silly but thrilling superhero free-for-all.
critic.name: M.V. Moorhead
publication.name: Phoenix Magazine

quote: You would think they would go back to a time when Thanos was young and vulnerable and off him. They opt for a more intricate approach, which bored me.
critic.name: Phumlani S Langa
publication.name: City Press (South Africa)

quote: Avengers: Infinity War at least had the good taste to abstain from Jeremy Renner. No such luck in Endgame.
critic.name: Daniel Barnes
publication.name: Sacramento News & Review

quote: As expected, the film is carried by the original six Avengers, but it does a remarkable job of bringing virtually every memorable character from all 22 movies back onto the screen. It is a staggering reminder of past and present pleasures.
critic.name: Stefan Kyriazis
publication.name: Daily Express (UK)

quote: Endgame definitively closes a few chapters in the Avengers saga in highly satisfying fashion. It is a tremendously entertaining intergalactic trip.
critic.name: Kara Warner
publication.name: People Magazine

quote: It is this part of the story, the human side, to narrow it down to our marginal planet, that holds the movie together for its three-hour run time.
critic.name: Stephen Romei
publication.name: The Australian

quote: Though it takes far too long to get going (the early scenes are needlessly repetitive and this would have been sharper as a 140 minute movie or somesuch), once it's up and running it's full of thrills.
critic.name: Nathaniel Rogers
publication.name: The Film Experience

quote: While the supporting cast members often feel like benched players, the remaining Avengers' arcs do, for the most part, pay off the stories the set up by the film's first hour.
critic.name: Siddhant Adlakha
publication.name: Slashfilm

quote: There will never be a Marvel film with an epic feel like this one. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Manuel Piñón
publication.name: Fotogramas

quote: An emotional, fulfilling ride...
critic.name: Michael Rougeau
publication.name: GameSpot

quote: Endgame does what all the great Marvel movies do-it's a fun and funny action movie made by people who are experts at doing just that. But it's impossible not to be frustrated with how Marvel stumbled on the landing...
critic.name: Matt Miller
publication.name: Esquire Magazine

quote: ...chock full of maudlin eddies that should have been pared back. That said, Endgame gets the job done, passing the baton as it closes out a long-running chapter with some sentimental eye rubs.
critic.name: Tom Meek
publication.name: Cambridge Day

quote: The stakes to deliver a fitting finale to the Infinity Saga are immense. But Avengers: Endgame is so darn satisfying, it will be hard to find a blockbuster that will match its emotionality or excitement.
critic.name: Katie Smith-Wong
publication.name: Flick Feast

quote: To paraphrase Thanos, Oscar nominations are inevitable.
critic.name: Bruce R. Miller
publication.name: Sioux City Journal

quote: The directing team of Anthony and Joe Russo has found just the right vein of showmanship and self-deprecation to bring the saga to a satisfying close.
critic.name: Tom Shone
publication.name: Sunday Times (UK)

quote: I feel like Stan Lee is probably looking down from heaven with a huge smile on his face with Avengers: Endgame
critic.name: Paul McGuire Grimes
publication.name: KSTP-TV (St. Paul, MN)

quote: As the dust clears, Disney stands like Thanos astride Earth-616. They have won, but what kind of world is left behind?
critic.name: Chris McCoy
publication.name: Memphis Flyer

quote: This is a feat of engineering... I felt a sense of catharsis finishing it.
critic.name: Amy Nicholson
publication.name: FilmWeek (KPCC - NPR Los Angeles)

quote: You wonder how so much talent, underwritten by such an obscenely large budget, doesn't trigger more pathos.
critic.name: Jason Di Rosso
publication.name: ABC News (Australia)

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a masterpiece which not only delivers on every expectation you had but exceeds ones you didn't even think about. This isn't just a movie, it's an experience.
critic.name: Josh Wilding
publication.name: ComicBookMovie.com

quote: Endgame is quite simply everything you need it to be, and everything I wanted it to be.
critic.name: Kate Rodger
publication.name: Newshub (NZ)

quote: Avengers: Endgame is REAL great ... with an emphasis on real. Would have been my first 10 rated review ... but they killed my favorite heroes. 'Cheeseburgers...'
critic.name: Vincent Schilling
publication.name: Indian Country Today

quote: Endgame fails its female characters by devaluing them and forgets its characters of color entirely.
critic.name: Dana Sloane
publication.name: Mediaversity Reviews

quote: It does justice to an ending that's 22 movies in the making.
critic.name: Brian Lloyd
publication.name: entertainment.ie

quote: Avengers: Endgame is an epic, emotional, spectacle-driven farewell to the Marvel Cinematic Universe as we know it. And the fact that it is so clearly an end is part of the reason it's so successful.
critic.name: Karl Delossantos
publication.name: Smash Cut Reviews

quote: Avengers: Endgame is almost certainly better than you expect, and far more satisfying and entertaining than its predecessor.
critic.name: Oscar Goff
publication.name: Boston Hassle

quote: Avengers: Endgame is better and more nourishing than Infinity War, but it's still the same long con.
critic.name: Dominic Griffin
publication.name: Spectrum Culture

quote: With Avengers: Endgame, it some ways they've made the most adult superhero film yet. Because there are consequences. And things matter.
critic.name: Stuart McGurk
publication.name: GQ Magazine [UK]

quote: To compare to Infinity War, I think that Endgame has the better storyline, the more satisfying conclusion, better conclusion, and much richer emotions.
critic.name: Sean Chandler
publication.name: Sean Chandler Talks About

quote: [Avengers: Endgame] is a very fitting conclusion to Phase 1, 2 and 3 of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. Bring a box of tissues, because it's an emotional roller coaster ride.
critic.name: John Nguyen
publication.name: Nerd Reactor

quote: Avengers: Endgame doesn't disappoint. There is so much to absorb that one sitting isn't enough.
critic.name: Allison Rose
publication.name: FlickDirect

quote: Avengers: Endgame is both a farewell and a celebration of 11 years of the audacious and wildly successful Marvel Studios experiment. It's very good at both of those things.
critic.name: Joshua Rivera
publication.name: GQ

quote: Naysayers suggest that Marvel dominance of this cinematic age will one day feel goofy. That opinion is insane. A generation has grown up with these films as their cultural spinal column. They will no more outgrow them than our bodies shed vertebrae.
critic.name: Ryan Syrek
publication.name: The Reader (Omaha, NE)

quote: Better than it has any right to be, this post-apocalyptic superhero film has significantly more merits than demerits.
critic.name: Wesley Lovell
publication.name: Cinema Sight

quote: For those of us who have been there from the beginning, the three-plus hours went by without me once looking at my watch. I enjoyed how it delved more deeply into the characters with terrific back-and-forth banter of old friends.
critic.name: Diane Pershing
publication.name: Malibu Times

quote: The late unsuperness of our heroes may be a real guide, a source of hope rather than disappointment.
critic.name: Michael Wood
publication.name: London Review of Books

quote: The entire tone of the film felt like a eulogy to the MCU and relied too heavily on weepy eyed nostalgia and fan service moments to carry it to the end.
critic.name: Alachia Queen
publication.name: Alachia Queen

quote: While the experience is bittersweet, the creative team brings everything to a close with a strong, well-meaning and ultimately heartfelt movie.
critic.name: Kimberly Pierce
publication.name: Geek Girl Authority

quote: It streamlined the narrative and didn't dredge up the bad writing of Age of Ultron, which is always a net positive.
critic.name: Kate Gardner
publication.name: The Mary Sue

quote: At the end of Endgame is the satisfaction that audiences are witness to an entertaining adventure. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Luis Fernando Galván
publication.name: En Filme

quote: 'Avengers: Endgame' is a fitting finale for the end of a Marvel era.
critic.name: Linda Cook
publication.name: Quad City Times (Davenport, IA)

quote: The final movie in Marvel's Infinity Saga is a masterpiece. It's an absolute spectacle. It's a love letter to fans of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. Laughs. Tears. Applause. Avengers: Endgame gets all of it.
critic.name: Brandon Davis
publication.name: ComicBook.com

quote: That it succeeds isn't a surprise... The real surprise -- to the relief of many -- is the level of quality to which this complicated and admittedly busy piece of pop art rises.
critic.name: Gary Dowell
publication.name: Dark Horizons

quote: It's official. We've been had.
critic.name: Chris Barsanti
publication.name: Eyes Wide Open

quote: Endgame is a truly special film, it is the culmination of years of hard work, which was all pieced together with such care and attention, I couldn't help but adore it.
critic.name: Siobhan Eardley
publication.name: Battle Royale With Cheese

quote: Sadly, our rating system only goes up to five, because otherwise I'd give "Avengers: Endgame" six!
critic.name: Michael A. Smith
publication.name: MediaMikes

quote: The movie is touching and emotional, with great action, friendship, unconditional love and farewell scenes. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fausto Ponce
publication.name: Proceso

quote: Game over man, game over!
critic.name: Richard Bonaduce
publication.name: Salt Lake Magazine

quote: Endgame is a celebration of everything that's gone before, stuffed with callbacks and unexpected and unlikely cameos that will reward hardcore fans in spades.
critic.name: Abigail Chandler
publication.name: SciFiNow

quote: The Endgame's plot is not exactly innovative, and the structure is uneven, but its sense of humor is an authentic triumph. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Alejandro Alemán
publication.name: El Universal

quote: Amusing, engrossing, exhilarating, visually spectacular, fast paced, and fairly breezy for a movie that is three hours in length...
critic.name: Sameen Amer
publication.name: The News International (Pakistan)

quote: No sequence is a better analog for the pic's ups and downs than its climactic, supersized fight scene, one that amazes one moment and baffles the next.
critic.name: J. Olson
publication.name: Cinemixtape

quote: It's hard to deny that the Infinity Saga has been an incredibly singular achievement, and Endgame is the finale it has always deserved.
critic.name: Matthew Lucas
publication.name: The Dispatch (Lexington, NC)

quote: Maybe it's the best ... That the children enjoy their party. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Vicente Gutiérrez
publication.name: El Economista

quote: Endgame is not exactly an inspired finish, but it's certainly true to Marvel form, an extensive extravaganza armed with an intuitive grasp of its audience's needs and desires.
critic.name: Aaron Leggo
publication.name: Sloths and Movies

quote: The end feels quite as it should feel. And the ultimate clash is as epic as we thought it would be. [Full review in Spanish].
critic.name: Federico Furzan
publication.name: Cinelipsis

quote: With a spectacularly unjustified running time of 182 minutes, the film finds room to pack in just about every kind of tonality that a Marvel movie has ever trafficked in.
critic.name: Tim Brayton
publication.name: Alternate Ending

quote: With plenty of surprises and the right mix between comedy and drama, Avengers: Endgame lives up to its hype
critic.name: Matthew Toomey
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)

quote: They created a tone within this universe that was set and to-the-point...they made that turn, and they landed it, masterfully.
critic.name: Justin Brown
publication.name: Medium Popcorn

quote: One of the best movies I've ever seen. One of the best payoffs...I was not disappointed.
critic.name: Brandon Collins
publication.name: Medium Popcorn

quote: So, much to my surprise, I liked this, even at three hours.
critic.name: Christopher Llewellyn Reed
publication.name: Reel Talk with Christopher Llewellyn Reed

quote: Mind-blowing and nail-biting doesn't begin to describe it as the biggest assemblage of Avengers we have seen approach endgame, to provide the perfect send-off for the billions of fans worldwide who have been with them all the way.
critic.name: Paula Fleri-Soler
publication.name: Times of Malta

quote: what I found most impressive about Endgame is how is just as often strikes notes of grace as it does moments of hectic violence
critic.name: James Kendrick
publication.name: Q Network Film Desk

quote: The main takeaway of Avengers: Endgame is the presumption that the half that remained may listen to their better angels. Forget time travel, the real fairy-tale lays here.
critic.name: Jorge Ignacio Castillo
publication.name: Prairie Dog Magazine

quote: It's revealing that after 22 movies packed with action and fantasy, the franchise chose to end its narrative with a small moment of intimacy and sweetness. [Full review in Portuguese]
critic.name: Pablo Villaça
publication.name: Cinema em Cena

quote: Yes, it's long, but it's rare to find a three-hour film that moves with the velocity of "Endgame." It's certainly a winner.
critic.name: Christopher Schobert
publication.name: Filmswoon

quote: The MCU pictures have always stressed that neither the destination nor the journey are as important as the connections we make along the way. As this is already the most lucrative series ever, clearly that message has struck a chord with millions.
critic.name: Samuel R. Murrian
publication.name: Parade Magazine

quote: I've already seen it twice, and I want to see it again...a lot of good moments, just great stuff. Thank you, Marvel, and everyone who worked on these movies.
critic.name: Andre Meadows
publication.name: Black Nerd Comedy

quote: Afterwards, your belly will be full of superhero goodness.
critic.name: Bob Grimm
publication.name: Reno News and Review

quote: Is it the best superhero movie ever made? In the words of Balki Bartokomous, "Don't be ridiculous." (The plotholes are prominent enough to make me consider dropping the rating a half-star.) Nevertheless, this ranks among the upper echelons of the MCU.
critic.name: Matt Brunson
publication.name: Film Frenzy

quote: An expansive story, a large and unwieldy universe, plenty of knowing callbacks, the willing suspension of disbelief-and a setup for the next one...
critic.name: Micah Peters
publication.name: The Ringer

quote: The directors have created a virtual nesting doll of homages which will be appreciated by the most hardcore of fans, but still have value for less devoted fans.
critic.name: Ani Bundel
publication.name: NBC News THINK

quote: According to Buddhist/Taoist teachings, smaller-particle dimensions are where the heavens are actually located. This is one of the many reasons why "Avengers" movies are tales, that by definition, have to be about gods.
critic.name: Mark Jackson
publication.name: Epoch Times

quote: Avengers: Endgame is, in every way, Loki deficient. Otherwise, it's a pretty darn good movie.
critic.name: Eleanor Ringel Cater
publication.name: Saporta Report (Atlanta)

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a satisfying, expertly made sequel in the franchise and combines with Infinity War to create the MCU's best, most compelling storytelling.
critic.name: Matt Ward
publication.name: Cinematic Considerations

quote: One Avengers movie to bind them, and in the darkness rule them all.
critic.name: Robert Roten
publication.name: Laramie Movie Scope

quote: Endgame stands out as one of the most detailed, satisfying conclusions to a chapter in a long-running franchise.
critic.name: Annie Banks
publication.name: Cultured Vultures

quote: There's a lot of fun to be had with this blockbuster behemoth, especially for those who have avidly followed the franchise.
critic.name: Rich Cline
publication.name: Shadows on the Wall

quote: These broad-appeal movies have to please a lot of people just enough to keep us invested, and this one gets the job done.
critic.name: Molly Templeton
publication.name: Eugene Weekly (OR)

quote: An emotional journey that doesn't waste a minute. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Lucero Calderón
publication.name: Excelsior

quote: All the necessary heroes get the right amount of screen time and for every laugh there are other things happening to balance it all out.
critic.name: Paul Farren
publication.name: Film Ireland Magazine

quote: To see Endgame with a crowd is to remember what moviegoing once was and still can be: a group experience of grief and joy. It's a reason to assemble.
critic.name: Margot Harrison
publication.name: Seven Days

quote: It would be nearly unfathomable to have spent more than 20 preceding films with these characters and not feel anything at the end of the sometimes tedious, mostly satisfying Avengers: Endgame.
critic.name: Roxana Hadadi
publication.name: Chesapeake Family Magazine

quote: Endgame succeeds in offering its fans a very real sense of closure. And that's no small feat.
critic.name: Vicky Roach
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (Australia)

quote: A miraculous blend of grief and humor. Big, bold, brash, then sneakily meta. I am only starting to get my head around the emotional and creative right-hook of it. A fitting end (for now) to the MCU.
critic.name: MaryAnn Johanson
publication.name: Flick Filosopher

quote: What you will be getting when you walk into an inevitably overstuffed movie theater is something singular that reflects our age in a way that none of the MCU films that preceded it have-indeed, very few Hollywood spectacles ever have.
critic.name: Oliver Jones
publication.name: Observer

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a beautifully-constructed piece of popcorn cinema ... anyone who has given their time to this world will find it to be a rewarding and effective payoff.
critic.name: Allen Adams
publication.name: The Maine Edge

quote: Incredibly, the film completes a feat no one believed Marvel would be able to pull off 10 years ago-create a long-running arc of stories that spanned a catalog of films, and end it in a profoundly satisfying way.
critic.name: Monique Jones
publication.name: Just Add Color

quote: The word epic gets thrown around so much that we've forgotten what it actually means. This movie is here to remind you.
critic.name: Aaron Dicer
publication.name: Siftpop

quote: A spectacular, once-in-a-lifetime epic. Avengers, dismissed.
critic.name: Cameron Frew
publication.name: FrewFilm

quote: Some of the smarmy humour falls flat on its face, while other parts are surprisingly dark. All the same, you couldn't deny its sheer value for money.
critic.name: Hilary A White
publication.name: Sunday Independent (Ireland)

quote: As epic as you would expect and more. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: José Martín
publication.name: El antepenúltimo mohicano

quote: The film designs its moments wel. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: William Venegas
publication.name: La Nación (Costa Rica)

quote: "Endgame" is a paltry attempt to introduce true catastrophe and finality into its franchise when compared with more fearless and ground breaking epics.
critic.name: Dustin Chase
publication.name: Galveston Daily News

quote: The Marvel Cinematic Universe, up to this point, comes to an end with an installment that easily ranks among the best in the series...
critic.name: David Nusair
publication.name: Reel Film Reviews

quote: It is an escalator to nowhere rather than a definitive endgame.
critic.name: Damien Straker
publication.name: Impulse Gamer

quote: It dares to wrestle with big, existential issues, confront some surprisingly grown up questions and take enormous narrative risks.
critic.name: Wade Major
publication.name: CineGods.com

quote: Everything works. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Luis Martínez
publication.name: El Mundo (Spain)

quote: Despite the comic-book origins of the tale, the stakes feel real, with some powerful moments of sacrifice, and a few wistful reunions.
critic.name: Chris Knight
publication.name: National Post

quote: Chris Hemsworth walks off with the 3-hour cameo extravaganza. The talking rodent comes in second. Doesn't anybody deserve to die?
critic.name: Victoria Alexander
publication.name: Film Festival Today

quote: A perfect companion piece to Avengers: Infinity War, yet strong enough to stand alone as one of the best superhero films ever made.
critic.name: Lauren Veneziani
publication.name: WBAL-TV (Baltimore)

quote: The 3-hour culmination of 22 chapters in the Marvel Cinematic Universe is worth going back in time and watching again.
critic.name: Jordan Hoffman
publication.name: Times of Israel

quote: Thus comes to an end, 21 films and 11 years later, the most lucrative franchise in the history of cinema... There are notable ups and downs in [this] long journey, and the conclusion is no exception. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Hugo Hernández Valdivia
publication.name: Cinexcepción

quote: The titanic effort of all the actors, producers, directors and crew of all these films to pull off such a satisfying product is something worthy of praise. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Israel Acosta Aroche
publication.name: Konexión

quote: If, like me, you've seen all 21 films that precede it, you won't begrudge it a single second. Definitely worth assembling for.
critic.name: Matthew Bond
publication.name: The Mail on Sunday (UK)

quote: That final hour is a good final hour. Thanos is still, in my opinion, an excellent villain.
critic.name: Tony Baker
publication.name: Tony Baker Comedy

quote: What perhaps makes Endgame so special is that everyone involved -- including the very talented cast -- seem to understand that this is the first time where the story feels more like a conclusion than a continuation.
critic.name: Micheal Compton
publication.name: Bowling Green Daily News

quote: Looking better than ever with characters you've spent over a decade with, Avengers: Endgame manages to find an incredible balance between gut-wrenching character moments and truly fantastic action sequences.
critic.name: Damian Levy
publication.name: Jamaica Gleaner

quote: A wonderful surprise, filling almost each and every minute with excitement, drama, humor and visually interesting and entertaining intrigue.
critic.name: Pamela Powell
publication.name: Daily Journal (Kankakee, IL)

quote: Avengers: Endgame represents a remarkable achievement.
critic.name: Michael Burgin
publication.name: Paste Magazine

quote: No one can dispute the Russo Brothers's competence in directing. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Jordi Costa
publication.name: El Pais (Spain)

quote: A ten year journey ends in the most ambitious and emotive film to date. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Sergio López Aguirre
publication.name: Cine Premiere

quote: Endgame's true feat is how it flawlessly subverts our expectations without feeling like betrayal.
critic.name: Kent Garrison
publication.name: Mad About Movies Podcast

quote: Frigga has one of the funniest lines in the whole movie: "Son, eat more vegetables." Indeed, it is not terrible eat junk food from time to time, but we must eat healthier. The same goes for cinema. Endgame is junk food. The healthier cinema is elsewhere.
critic.name: Ernesto Diezmartinez
publication.name: Cine Vértigo

quote: A satisfying end to an era and worthy of its size and hype
critic.name: Stephen Silver
publication.name: Splice Today

quote: Avengers: Endgame will have fans singing its praises - and they should.
critic.name: Pete Hammond
publication.name: Deadline Hollywood Daily

quote: Triumphs through the strength of its storytelling, characters arcs, and visual spectacle. A perfectly imperfect epic of an ending - a closure of an era, a continuance and beginning of the next generation of superheroes.
critic.name: Nathalia Aryani
publication.name: The MovieMaven

quote: The only complaint about Avengers: Endgame is that it raises the bar so high that there may well never be a superhero movie to match it.
critic.name: Matthew Norman
publication.name: London Evening Standard

quote: What's missing from "Endgame" is the free play of imagination, the liberation of speculation, the meandering paths and loose ends that start in logic and lead to wonder.
critic.name: Richard Brody
publication.name: New Yorker

quote: [As] a finale to the MCU we've known since 2008's Iron Man, Avengers: Endgame is an exciting, fitting, substantial, almost miraculously eloquent closer.
critic.name: Blake Crane
publication.name: BlakeCrane.com

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a very real achievement and one that even serial dislikers of the MCU should pay grudging respect.
critic.name: Tim Brennan
publication.name: About Boulder

quote: Avengers: Endgame is as much a trip down MCU memory lane as it is the final chapter to a story that changed cinema forever.
critic.name: Courtney Small
publication.name: Cinema Axis

quote: Whatever your feelings about Disney's Borg-like assimilation of all entertainment, Endgame's synthesis of 22 movies' worth of characters/plot is nothing short of remarkable.
critic.name: Pete Vonder Haar
publication.name: Houston Press

quote: We won't talk about the technobabble inelegantly cited in a bid to hold it all together - the equivalent of taking out an airplane's jackscrews and replacing them with chewing gum.
critic.name: Ed Whitfield
publication.name: The Ooh Tray

quote: You'll never see a victory lap look quite as awesome as this one.
critic.name: Rob Vaux
publication.name: Sci-Fi Movie Page

quote: This is an emotionally-satisfying conclusion to this grand venture, featuring many moments that tug at the heartstrings, plenty of chuckles, and, of course, more action than anyone could ever want in a film.
critic.name: Jeff Beck
publication.name: The Blu Spot

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a spectacular conclusion to the Marvel Cinematic Universe's first era.
critic.name: Ian Thomas Malone
publication.name: Ian Thomas Malone

quote: [T]he Russo brothers defy expectations and give fans a movie they didn't anticipate, but will be grateful to have.
critic.name: Sarah Gopaul
publication.name: Digital Journal

quote: Emotional heft combines with a sweeping sense of the epic, often within the same scene.
critic.name: Sarah Cartland
publication.name: Caution Spoilers

quote: "Avengers Endgame" at its best-illustrates the qualities of being a true hero-all while Marvel's greatest cinematic hits are warmly and entertainingly revisited!
critic.name: Sarah Knight Adamson
publication.name: Sarah's Backstage Pass

quote: The final battle is giddily cathartic, but the catharsis arises from prioritising character development over plot and spectacle. This, I imagine, will be the Avengers' legacy.
critic.name: Simran Hans
publication.name: Observer (UK)

quote: This three-hour super-hero team-up is an action-packed, yet nostalgic, long goodbye - with no sly post-credit teasers.
critic.name: Susan Granger
publication.name: SSG Syndicate

quote: A high-octane spectacular filled with surprises, twists and action sequences that are pure mayhem. The film's conceit is as large as its scale.
critic.name: Louise Keller
publication.name: Urban Cinefile

quote: The MCU will go on and on, but this chapter - and the American pragmatism vs. American ideals bromance that drove it - have well and truly come to their "Excelsior! Nuff said!" moment.
critic.name: Matthew Lickona
publication.name: San Diego Reader

quote: Avengers Endgame is a bittersweet love letter to Marvel fans that ushers in a satisfying amount of closure.
critic.name: Emmanuel Noisette
publication.name: The Movie Blog

quote: So many characters and so much going on that I got worried Marvel would run out of characters and have to borrow a few from DC Comics. Fun flick, too long but fun.
critic.name: Gary Wolcott
publication.name: KXL-FM (Portland, OR)

quote: These films are essentially a bottle and a warm blanket in the thunderstorm of life. AVENGERS: ENDGAME pays complete fan service to our favorite moments.
critic.name: James Clay
publication.name: Fresh Fiction

quote: I was enthralled with the production. The costumes, makeup, set designs, sound, special and visual effects, stunts and Cinematography (Trent Opaloch) made this a fun and exciting movie
critic.name: Diana Saenger
publication.name: ReviewExpress.com

quote: ...a brilliant close to a chapter of filmmaking we will likely never see again in our lifetime.
critic.name: Michael Ward
publication.name: Should I See It

quote: Endgame is a summer camp goodbye-sad for the friends we won't see again, but happy for the time we got to spend together. Endgame makes sure it was time spent well.
critic.name: Sarah Marrs
publication.name: Lainey Gossip

quote: You will come for the characters & Story, get caught up in their journey, get excited about the action & leave with uncontained satisfaction. A laugh, a tear a cheer. A cinematic Marvel & the crown jewel of the Universe. A Must See! four out of 4 reels
critic.name: Reginald Ponder
publication.name: vocalo.org

quote: Despite early pacing struggles, Avengers: Endgame delivers on its promise to bring childhood dreams to life, with more than enough heart to spare.
critic.name: Aaron Peterson
publication.name: The Hollywood Outsider

quote: Overall, the fourth and final-not-final Avengers movie is full of emotion, much more than its predecessors, and rife with well-earned resolutions.
critic.name: Stephen Garrett
publication.name: Book & Film Globe

quote: It's an epic franchise finale that cuts straight to the heart of what it means to rise from the ashes of defeat.
critic.name: André Hereford
publication.name: Metro Weekly (Washington, DC)

quote: The Russo brothers, writers and cast really outdid themselves with this one, and this is evident in the witty script, multiple plot twists and scenes that will have you erupting in laughter or holding your breath.
critic.name: Carmelita Fredericks
publication.name: Independent Online (South Africa)

quote: The epic adventure has now come to its grand conclusion, with the 22nd film, Avengers: Endgame, and it should satisfy all fans of the series.
critic.name: Tatat Bunnag
publication.name: Bangkok Post

quote: It's fun to see all these character threads unravel, and knit up, as the movie waddles toward its big but indifferent climax of Avengers versus Thanos.
critic.name: Thelma Adams
publication.name: AARP Movies for Grownups

quote: Endgame consists almost entirely of the downtime scenes that were always secretly everyone's favorite parts of these movies anyway.
critic.name: Dana Stevens
publication.name: Slate

quote: 'Endgame' is more than a movie, it is an emotional event - a reward for loyalty, as well as a promise of new things to come.
critic.name: Bob Bloom
publication.name: Journal and Courier (Lafayette, IN)

quote: It feels like a curtain closing...there was an elegance in the way they moved toward conclusion. No fan is going to watch and feel short-changed.
critic.name: Mark Kermode
publication.name: Kermode & Mayo's Film Review

quote: ...A wonderful, rousing payoff in the context of the big battle and as wildly inspiring imagery.
critic.name: Perri Nemiroff
publication.name: Perri Nemiroff (YouTube)

quote: Avengers: Endgame makes you keenly aware of the passage of this time.
critic.name: Anupama Chopra
publication.name: Film Companion

quote: Emotionally satisfying, with lots of surprises...it wasn't just a good comic-book movie, just a good Marvel movie, but a genuinely full-stop good movie.
critic.name: Achara Kirk
publication.name: GET Jaby

quote: Very much worth the wait. That's all I need to say.
critic.name: Jaby Koay
publication.name: GET Jaby

quote: Superhero adventures are the predominant films of our time, and this one easily stands as the most significant.
critic.name: Mike McGranaghan
publication.name: Aisle Seat

quote: It's fun. You're not watching Shakespeare, remember...these guys have really done something with the superhero movie.
critic.name: Martin Thomas
publication.name: Double Toasted

quote: A movie with just so many great parts to it. I guarantee later, if part of it comes on, you'll stick around to watch the whole thing.
critic.name: Korey Coleman
publication.name: Double Toasted

quote: A rousing finale. Epic in scale and in heart.
critic.name: Chris Stuckmann
publication.name: ChrisStuckmann.com

quote: There's a lot of research to do. But it's fun homework.
critic.name: Mark Ellis
publication.name: Schmoes Know

quote: If you're a fan of these movies, I think you're going to be satisfied. It's a satisfying ending to this phase.
critic.name: Kristian Harloff
publication.name: Schmoes Know

quote: The Avengers as we know them will never reassemble and, in their wake, superhero movies will never be the same again.
critic.name: Mathew DeKinder
publication.name: Suburban Journals of St. Louis

quote: At its outset, Endgame is a dour bit of rockism-a testament to the power of earnest storytelling.
critic.name: Sean Fennessey
publication.name: The Ringer

quote: The film has Marvel bending, breaking their own rules. It's a bold move and should hopefully pay off.
critic.name: Devesh Sharma
publication.name: Filmfare

quote: Kudos to directors Anthony and Joe Russo just for keeping things organized, let alone coherent, which they also manage.
critic.name: Eric D. Snider
publication.name: Crooked Marquee

quote: There is lots to love here: the way Downey balances acerbic wit and heartfelt feeling. The way Ruffalo somehow manages to invest Hulk/Banner with warmth. Evans' all-American sincerity.
critic.name: Randall King
publication.name: Winnipeg Free Press

quote: Thank goodness for some fine ol' trademark, avenging humor saving the day and carrying us through much of the weltschmerz with almost a full two hours remaining in this really big show.
critic.name: John Urbancich
publication.name: Your Movies (cleveland.com)

quote: A sobering, galvanizing tribute to the sprawling franchise and especially the superheroes who anchor it.
critic.name: Annlee Ellingson
publication.name: L.A. Biz

quote: Suffice to say that Endgame lives up to its promise as a gratifying, if bittersweet goodbye to modern cinema's biggest superheroes.
critic.name: Melissa Leon
publication.name: The Daily Beast

quote: For the non-fans, the film's explanatory tone might come across as a speed breaker at times, but for the fans, the same invokes hope and excitement, leading to constant gasps and howls.
critic.name: Ronak Kotecha
publication.name: The Times of India

quote: t's really long; three hours long. There is a bit too much time travel. But overall it's just the kind of extravaganza you'd expect.
critic.name: Rashid Irani
publication.name: Hindustan Times

quote: Endgame is hugely ambitious, ridiculous, over-the-top superhero filmmaking and I loved it.
critic.name: Huw Fullerton
publication.name: Radio Times

quote: Endgame feels like a victory lap. It is a means of catharsis and a release for fans who have held their breath, awaiting the fate of their favourite heroes.
critic.name: Millicent Thomas
publication.name: Screen Queens

quote: Avengers: Endgame will alternately make you shed tears, giddy at the possibilities, excited for what's coming, whoop when you witness it, and nostalgic for the MCU past.
critic.name: Akhil Arora
publication.name: Gadgets360

quote: It's overdone and bombastic. A fitting end, in other words, to a franchise cycle of insatiable commercial ambition...and thundering creative swagger.
critic.name: Kevin Maher
publication.name: Times (UK)

quote: "Avengers: Endgame" is a classy end to a collection of films, but also one that makes the future of new Marvel movies look so bright that you can't help but smile.
critic.name: Michael Smith
publication.name: Tulsa World

quote: Avengers: Endgame succeeds in delivering both the epic scope such a finale demands, and the personal touches that have made the whole franchise so winning.
critic.name: Abbie Bernstein
publication.name: Assignment X

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a cinematic achievement unlike any other. And it is a gift... a thank you to those fans who have taken the journey.
critic.name: Rob Carnevale
publication.name: Indie London

quote: Proud postures alternate with callbacks and climaxes and sniffly tear-tugs and lots of that wacky, weightless Marvel verbal humor... telegraphic jolts of joy for those who [ingested] the prior 2,299 minutes of the "Universe" entire.
critic.name: Ray Pride
publication.name: Newcity

quote: A somewhat disjointed by satisfying conclusion to the first generation of Marvel films, filled with dashing spectacle and quiet character moments.
critic.name: Christopher Lloyd
publication.name: The Film Yap

quote: Talk about a curtain call.
critic.name: Kiko Martinez
publication.name: San Antonio Current

quote: 'Avengers: Endgame' is a well executed story that centers its characters and their journeys, while providing some of the best action sequences the MCU has ever had.
critic.name: Mae Abdulbaki
publication.name: Movies with Mae

quote: Endgame is not flawless... But goddamn if it still isn't great.
critic.name: TK Burton
publication.name: Pajiba

quote: This is fan service elevated into an art form, transcending winking self-aggrandisement to become something of a reflection on the past eleven years, a chugging, tooting, spectacular train of a franchise, careering indefinitely forward.
critic.name: Christopher Machell
publication.name: CineVue

quote: Not terrible, sometimes fun, long, dark, dim and predictable.
critic.name: James Verniere
publication.name: Boston Herald

quote: In other words, without a diversity of voices, what are doubtless good intentions feel like paternalistic tokenism. It wouldn't be as frustrating if the solution weren't obvious.
critic.name: Walter Chaw
publication.name: Film Freak Central

quote: Spoiler-filled review: Endgame begins and ends with quiet, intimate moments. And it's that sense of intimacy that makes this galaxy-spanning blockbuster such a triumph.
critic.name: Richard Trenholm
publication.name: CNET

quote: Avengers: Endgame culminates the MCU with a swan song that celebrates its rich history and provides a heartfelt conclusion 22 films in the making.
critic.name: Sheraz Farooqi
publication.name: CinemaDebate

quote: Endgame's three-hour length suggests profundity, but each bout of knuckle-busting between the specially gifted vigilantes and the demonic Thanos either panders or, at best, is merely redundant.
critic.name: Armond White
publication.name: National Review

quote: In producing a film as affecting and carefully crafted as this, Marvel is bestowing upon their audience the fulfilling sense that their love of these stories isn't just childish, escapist nerdism.
critic.name: Piers Marchant
publication.name: Arkansas Democrat-Gazette

quote: Faithful to its core, dense and rich, nostalgic and yet new, it reaches far and succeeds with all the elements the fans will love.
critic.name: Anne Brodie
publication.name: What She Said

quote: Purposeful chaos with a sleek finesse.
critic.name: Allyson Johnson
publication.name: The Young Folks

quote: Avengers: Endgame should make a lot of people happy for about three hours and one minute, solid. It's all that audiences could have possibly hoped for.
critic.name: Dwight Brown
publication.name: National Newspaper Publishers Association

quote: The characters, and the actors playing them, make this an exercise in pure popcorn fantasy doused in just enough sentiment to keep us engaged between wisecracks and yet another eye-popping effect.
critic.name: Andrea Chase
publication.name: Killer Movie Reviews

quote: There is, however, a boldness to the way the film attempts and succeeds in making a fantasy about unwinding the end of the world that's really about the fact that everyone still has to deal with having lived through it.
critic.name: Bob Chipman
publication.name: Escapist Magazine

quote: It would be accurate to say that a lot of the film is designed for crowd-pleasing, but that is nowhere near saying that it panders to fans. The film celebrates and revels in the franchise without seeming self-indulgent.
critic.name: Alex Doenau
publication.name: Trespass

quote: The pieces may all fit together like a mammoth jigsaw puzzle, but what's sorely lacking is spontaneity, that final-chapter frisson of anything-goes tension.
critic.name: Rubén Rosario
publication.name: MiamiArtZine

quote: For now this film delivers the popcorn experience devotees have anxiously waited for. General audiences can also bask in the fun and glory.
critic.name: Alci Rengifo
publication.name: Entertainment Voice

quote: Two and a half hours of plot for thirty minutes of magically divine statuesque iconography that's, surprisingly, worth the seat.
critic.name: Bill Arceneaux
publication.name: Big Easy Magazine

quote: The MCU has generally successfully balanced planetary and personal stakes. Endgame is a worthy culmination of that storytelling approach.
critic.name: Adam Kempenaar
publication.name: Filmspotting

quote: Not as visceral or intense as Infinity War - and not entirely satisfying - but there's still plenty to get excited about.
critic.name: Matt Hudson
publication.name: What I Watched Tonight

quote: You know things are pretty damn serious when Captain America starts swearing.
critic.name: Johnny Gayzmonic
publication.name: Fanboys of the Universe

quote: Avengers: Endgame dazzles, frazzles, exasperates but never relents.
critic.name: Wendy Shreve
publication.name: Featuring Film

quote: A masterful bombardment of everything that has made the Marvel Cinematic Universe films so impactful.
critic.name: Phil Villarreal
publication.name: ABC Tucson

quote: Fan service is the main course in the latest MCU extravaganza. Endgame revels in Marvel knowledge, and after 11 years and 22 films, most fans will be more than happy to indulge in it. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Mario Alegre
publication.name: Próxima Tanda

quote: The resulting chaos is still punctuated by the suspense, melodrama, and heroism necessary to provide gratifying closure to one of cinema's greatest serial storytelling feats.
critic.name: Jared Mobarak
publication.name: The Film Stage

quote: Overall, Avengers: Endgameis an unflinching and beautiful love letter to both comic books and the fans who have sustained the MCU.
critic.name: Kate Sánchez
publication.name: But Why Tho? A Geek Community

quote: There are horror movies and political dramas with premises less nightmarish than the one in "Avengers: Endgame... This is an interesting approach for a superhero film to take.
critic.name: Matthew Rozsa
publication.name: Salon.com

quote: You can easily duck out during the middle hour, do some shopping, and slip back into your seat for the climax. You won't have missed a thing.
critic.name: Anthony Lane
publication.name: New Yorker

quote: Rounding the bend into hour three, I heard a snurfling sound to my right. A discreet peek revealed that the guy next to me was semi-weeping, blotting away the odd tear with his shirt sleeve. Jeez, I thought. And then I realized...never mind.
critic.name: Kurt Loder
publication.name: Reason Online

quote: A decade of Marvel movies culminates in three hours of (awesome) fan service.
critic.name: Sonny Bunch
publication.name: Washington Free Beacon

quote: It's simultaneously a beautiful send-off, a greatest hits tour and a lap of honour. This is Marvel celebrating Marvel, and it is thoroughly deserved.
critic.name: Matt Looker
publication.name: TheShiznit.co.uk

quote: Just about the best send-off imaginable, a stunning achievement in blockbuster cinema and a satisfying resolution to a phenomenal run of films.
critic.name: Matthew Turner
publication.name: Hero Collector

quote: Where Infinity War was all bombast, Endgame offers reserve. Where Infinity War wrought intergalactic devastation and destruction, Endgame delivers intimacy and an examination of grief, loss and very private regret.
critic.name: Tom Glasson
publication.name: Concrete Playground

quote: The Superhero film has truly become our Western.
critic.name: Joel Mayward
publication.name: Cinemayward

quote: Messrs. Downey, Evans, et al, give their all to lift up the overlong AVENGERS: ENDGAME from its sloppy script and poor pacing, to leave their fans with unforgettable memories of their fractured, flawed, courageous heroes.
critic.name: Diva Velez
publication.name: TheDivaReview.com

quote: A fantastic full stop to a 22 film series, giving us some closure to an era of cinema, but still leaving a well-lived-in Earth for new adventures to be created going forward.
critic.name: David Hogan
publication.name: hoganreviews.co.uk

quote: ...for that first hour, Endgame is maybe the most radical superhero film since Logan...
critic.name: Matthew Dougherty
publication.name: The Filtered Lens

quote: A truly incredible and virtually unparalleled moviegoing experience that I can't wait to have again as soon as possible and many more times beyond that...Mission accomplished.
critic.name: Colby Bryant
publication.name: Colbybryant.com

quote: This movie is slow, steeped in nostalgia for the previous chapters, and very serious about itself.
critic.name: Robert Horton
publication.name: HeraldNet (Everett, WA)

quote: A beautiful, masterful final bow for the audience that has followed this epic story line from "Iron Man" and on.
critic.name: Felix Vasquez Jr.
publication.name: Cinema Crazed

quote: It's everything you should expect from the culmination of more than ten years of movies, especially if you've been following them from the beginning. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Sebastian Zavala Kahn
publication.name: Cinencuentro

quote: Despite being the longest superhero film in history, and the longest film in the MCU, Avengers: Endgame is paced like Quicksilver on crack cocaine.
critic.name: Rohan Naahar
publication.name: Hindustan Times

quote: If there were ever a movie designed to please its target audience, Endgame is an emblematic example. Anthony & Joe Russo manage to juggle the many components of this mosaic with finesse, & despite the outsized running time the movie seldom lags.
critic.name: Leonard Maltin
publication.name: leonardmaltin.com

quote: ... Endgame [is] as much of a love letter to the fans as it is a comic book fan's dream.
critic.name: Douglas Davidson
publication.name: Elements of Madness

quote: No matter how much homework you've done, what actually happens, the order in which it happens and the folks to whom it happens will still pack surprises - also tongue-in-cheekiness and quite a bit of lump-in-throatiness.
critic.name: Bob Mondello
publication.name: NPR

quote: An ambitious, emotional and satisfactory conclusion to the saga. A love letter to fans of the genre and followers of the whole franchise. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Fico Cangiano
publication.name: CineXpress

quote: [F]or the first 30 minutes or so ... [t]here's so much gloom, doom, and clinical depression among the remaining team you'd think you were watching a DC movie.
critic.name: Rain Jokinen
publication.name: MullingMovies.com

quote: The sheer force of the film ... is enough to make traditional complaints moot. Against significant odds, it's a fitting culmination to the biggest movie series in history.
critic.name: Sean Collier
publication.name: Pittsburgh Magazine

quote: A perfect ending to a Marvelous saga.
critic.name: Charles Koplinski
publication.name: Illinois Times

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a crowd-pleaser at the highest level, striking the perfect balance of paying homage to its predecessors and giving each character his/her moment to shine.
critic.name: Lauren Bradshaw
publication.name: Cloture Club

quote: An emotional and exciting show of gratitude to all the fans that have stuck with the MCU for 11 years. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Orlando Maldonado
publication.name: Movie Network

quote: The climactic war is more than just a CGI-laden smash-fest. Every corner of the chaos, every maneuver and turn, represent an important moment in the lives of the characters.
critic.name: Jeffrey M. Anderson
publication.name: San Francisco Examiner

quote: Avengers: Endgame isn't a great movie ... but it's a beautiful and fitting swan song to a unique journey that forever changed the movie industry and the lives of so many fans.
critic.name: Rob Dean
publication.name: Bullz-Eye.com

quote: Overall Endgame"delivers what it needs to. Although three hours long, it never felt slow or draggy thanks to a narrative that is constantly cross-cutting between multiple storylines.
critic.name: Beth Accomando
publication.name: KPBS.org

quote: A beautifully heartbreaking ending to a saga.
critic.name: Ben Rolph
publication.name: Discussing Film

quote: After a payoff like this, it's fair to ask where the genre goes from here. This will be a very tough act - if not an impossible one - to follow.
critic.name: Daniel M. Kimmel
publication.name: North Shore Movies

quote: Boy, do directors Joe and Anthony Russo ensure the tale of space good and evil goes out with a hugely entertaining bang. Queries are answered, plot points tied up, justice is done.
critic.name: Alison Rowat
publication.name: The Herald (Scotland)

quote: Well. That was not what I expected. And, I think I love it all the more for it.
critic.name: Theresa Smith
publication.name: Weekend Special (South Africa)

quote: If you leave this film not once having felt your eyes heat up, or having your vision distort as a tear wells in your eye, you might just be Thanos.
critic.name: Jonathan Roberts
publication.name: The New Paper (Singapore)

quote: When the set pieces do come, audiences won't be disappointed. The final battle scene is a climax worthy of bringing this monumental 22-film chapter in the MCU to a close.
critic.name: Chris Newbould
publication.name: The National (UAE)

quote: Endgame has a few tricks up its sleeves that keep going right back to the heart.
critic.name: Richard Whittaker
publication.name: Austin Chronicle

quote: Marvel has clearly saved the best for last and I cannot stress how much those fan service moments will have you cheering.
critic.name: Chris Gore
publication.name: Film Threat

quote: Hitting its every note with expert precision, it's a triumph of humorous, action-packed, poignant blockbuster filmmaking.
critic.name: Nick Schager
publication.name: The Daily Beast

quote: There's something new in "Avengers Endgame." Real stakes. Also, real warmth, zest and a real sense of family connection.
critic.name: Asher Luberto
publication.name: culturevulture.net

quote: What a film.
critic.name: Patrick Lenton
publication.name: Junkee

quote: A film that should feel overlong and overstuffed rings purposeful, weighted with existential truth even as it flashes before our eyes.
critic.name: Leah Pickett
publication.name: Chicago Reader

quote: Avengers: Endgame is exceptional because it has the only thing that the MCU lacked until now: a closure, a sort of conclusion that really feels like the end of an era, and the beginning of a new one. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Pablo Fernandez
publication.name: Vix

quote: This is one of those movies you have to watch in the cinema with other people. You won't regret it.
critic.name: Jamal Grootboom
publication.name: Independent Online (South Africa)

quote: While Endgame never climbs new comic territory like its predecessors and is more often than not sombre and reflective, it is also narratively unlike any MCU film you've ever seen.
critic.name: Shyama Krishna Kumar
publication.name: Gulf News (UAE)

quote: Avengers: Endgame goes to great lengths to deliver what its fanbase expects: big battles with cosmic stakes, a bit of self-deprecation and a plethora of superheroes that are happily and reverentially showcased.
critic.name: Robert Denerstein
publication.name: Denerstein Unleashed

quote: this screenplay - be it out of necessity or design - might be the most inventive film in the Marvel canon, able to navigate a creative triptych through the annals of MCU lore without a bunch of forced flashbacks or awkward cameos
critic.name: Jason McKiernan
publication.name: Film Racket

quote: I cheered so hard. There are some scenes...prepare yourself. This movie made me feel whole.
critic.name: Steph Cozza
publication.name: Aggressive Comix

quote: The melancholy of Avengers: Endgame will last in the fans' emotional memory. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Pablo O. Scholz
publication.name: Clarín

quote: It's a beautiful farewell to the original Avengers, but also a perfect start for a new team. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Abigail Camarillo
publication.name: Chilango.com

quote: In a franchise that often resembles one exhausting run-on sentence, Avengers: Endgame feels like a welcome period (or at least a semicolon).
critic.name: Andrew Wyatt
publication.name: The Lens

quote: The film will have you laughing, jumping out of your seat, and an emotional wreck, often in the same beats. What a time to be alive to see a movie like this.
critic.name: Terence Johnson
publication.name: Le Noir Auteur

quote: It was always a bit touch and go just how Marvel would recover from the events of Infinity War and wrap up the stories of beloved heroes which we've been following for years, but they've done an impressive job which will leave fans entirely satisfied.
critic.name: Siena Yates
publication.name: New Zealand Herald

quote: No film has quite made me feel so emotionally in awe since The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King.
critic.name: Jennifer Heaton
publication.name: Alternative Lens

quote: Based on the screening I attended, I'd wager fans are unlikely to be disappointed: There were grown men and women weeping in the seats alongside me.
critic.name: Anousha Sakoui
publication.name: Bloomberg News

quote: Avengers: Endgame didn't seem a moment too long, and there wasn't an awkward performance among its cast.
critic.name: Richard von Busack
publication.name: MetroActive

quote: It gives us a collection of compelling characters, ties up a lot of loose ends, provides the satisfying pow and wow of a superhero movie, but then takes it all to another level, delivering a poignant drama with relatable human emotions.
critic.name: Clint O'Connor
publication.name: Akron Beacon Journal

quote: Satisfying and significant
critic.name: Michael J. Casey
publication.name: Boulder Weekly

quote: Despite all the whiz-bang CGI effects, some more special than others, the moments I most appreciated in Endgame were the small-scale comic touches... Best of all is Robert Downey Jr.
critic.name: Peter Rainer
publication.name: Christian Science Monitor

quote: "Avengers: Endgame" represents one of the best films in the MCU canon and provides an epic and emotionally satisfying finale to the characters we've grown with over the last ten years.
critic.name: Nate Adams
publication.name: The Only Critic

quote: Builds to an impressively ambitious finale, highlighting both the strengths and the limitations of the franchise as a whole.
critic.name: Steven D. Greydanus
publication.name: National Catholic Register

quote: The biggest box Endgame needed to check was to do justice to the array of personalities that audiences have come to love. Even given the three-hour runtime, its success in giving all of them their due is no mean feat.
critic.name: Megan Basham
publication.name: WORLD

quote: After more than a decade and ... 22 movies, that [nostalgic] impulse is understandable. It also feels a bit too easy, a little underwhelming, and more than a pinch manipulative.
critic.name: Mark Dujsik
publication.name: Mark Reviews Movies

quote: Despite a few shortcomings, Avengers: Endgame is still an affectionate, enjoyable closing chapter for a long-standing series.
critic.name: Abby Olcese
publication.name: Rave Reviews

quote: The last-reel battle pretty much has to be the most satisfying superhero movie set piece of all time, delivering the multiple closures this long-in-the-telling saga needs.
critic.name: Kim Newman
publication.name: Sight & Sound

quote: Spellbinding, surprising, and immensely satisfying. Eleven years, twenty-two films, one singular cinematic achievement the likes of which we've never seen before and aren't likely to again for a long time to come
critic.name: Zaki Hasan
publication.name: Zaki's Corner

quote: A grand finale that almost lives up to the anticipation levels that have built up around this monster set of stories.
critic.name: Bill Watters
publication.name: Bleeding Cool

quote: Infinity War may have proved that Marvel can pull off a massive superhero crossover event, but Endgame shows how much better these movies are when they pay attention to people, too.
critic.name: Jesse Hassenger
publication.name: The Week

quote: For a three-hour movie, "Endgame" is anything but bloated, with a wealth of poetic and pleasing moments.
critic.name: Josh Terry
publication.name: Deseret News (Salt Lake City)

quote: "Endgame" sticks this landing in ways that are thrilling, funny and emotional, and it does it by executing both on story and characters.
critic.name: Brad Keefe
publication.name: Columbus Alive

quote: What you will witness on that big silver screen is going to be a marvel to behold (pun intended).
critic.name: Garrett Green
publication.name: Black Nerd Problems

quote: The fantastic 'Avengers: Endgame' entertains with a vengeance.
critic.name: Roger Tennis
publication.name: Cinemaclips.com

quote: Predictable and...overstuffed with snarky lines and bathetic moments, though as sumptuously made as anything to have rolled off the Marvel assembly line [but] since it gives series fans a heaping helping of what they obviously savor, they'll eat it up.
critic.name: Frank Swietek
publication.name: One Guy's Opinion

quote: Endgame is a totally unique, brilliant cinematic experience.
critic.name: Owen Richards
publication.name: The Arts Desk

quote: ...provides something truly satisfying: a sense of closure.
critic.name: Josh Larsen
publication.name: LarsenOnFilm

quote: The culmination of the past 11 years and 21 films from Marvel Studios, Endgame hits all the emotional levels and brilliantly captures that comic book magic.
critic.name: Matt Rodriguez
publication.name: Shakefire

quote: Spoiler Free Review. The Avengers Assemble for one last epic, spectacular outing. Avengers: Endgame is indeed everything that hardcore fans could hope for
critic.name: Jazz Tangcay
publication.name: Awards Daily

quote: Avengers: Endgame feels like the blockbuster to end all blockbusters.
critic.name: Larushka Ivan-Zadeh
publication.name: Metro Newspaper (UK)

quote: Kudos to Anthony and Joe Russo for so elegantly tying together 21 movies and 25 heroes, giving poignant and satisfying send-offs to some, fresh new beginnings to others.
critic.name: Lisa Johnson Mandell
publication.name: AtHomeInHollywood.com

quote: The end of an era, done exactly as you'd hoped.
critic.name: Jamie East
publication.name: The Sun (UK)

quote: Quit reading this review and get yourself to a movie theater!
critic.name: Maren Longbella
publication.name: St. Paul Pioneer Press

quote: It's an episodic movie, so it shines in parts, rather than as a whole, but there are plenty of good parts.
critic.name: Chris Hewitt
publication.name: Minneapolis Star Tribune

quote: Endgame is good, rollicking fun, entertaining to the last drop with dollops of humour and comic-book pathos. That said, it's no soul-shaking masterpiece. Along with it likely being the biggest film of the year Endgame might also be the most overrated.
critic.name: Jim Schembri
publication.name: 3AW

quote: The MCU's long goodbye to the Avengers (is it really?) comes off as truly epic and thunderously exciting. But here's the big surprise-it's also an emotional wipeout .
critic.name: Peter Travers
publication.name: Rolling Stone

quote: Avengers: Endgame isn't as brash, surprising, or relentless as its predecessor but it's a worthy conclusion to the Infinity War duology and provides a satisfying end to the First Avengers Era.
critic.name: James Berardinelli
publication.name: ReelViews

quote: Avengers: Endgame isn't a perfect film yet the Russo Brothers, writers, and cast managed to create a movie that serves as a wholly satisfying send-off to some of the most beloved characters in the Marvel Cinematic Universe.
critic.name: Scott Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: The mega-franchise's biggest fans will likely embrace the waterlogged sentimentality that pervades the entire three-hour affair. But where does that leave those of us who just wanted a good movie?
critic.name: David Bax
publication.name: Battleship Pretension

quote: AVENGERS: ENDGAME is beyond your wildest dreams --- a charming, hilarious and often poignant source of IMMENSE entertainment!
critic.name: Jeanne Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: If I think that AVENGERS: ENDGAME is an amazing and wholly entertaining event, imagine what the enthusiastic fan base of MCU will think?
critic.name: David Kaplan
publication.name: Kaplan vs. Kaplan

quote: Despite usually being a passive moviegoer, I found myself cheering mid-scene, crying for an embarrassingly long portion of the runtime, and leaving the cinema completely blown away.
critic.name: Ciaran Kerr
publication.name: Film Bunker

quote: I might be tempted to describe Infinity War and Endgame as a couple of the worst and ideologically vacuous blockbuster movies ever made - except I'm no longer sure they should even be called movies
critic.name: Luke Buckmaster
publication.name: The Daily Review/Crikey

quote: The whole piece comes together almost seamlessly, a tapestry of Marvel's history, its waning present, and its waiting future.
critic.name: Michal Schick
publication.name: Hypable

quote: ENDGAME is not what you're expecting, yet it's also exactly the impressive epic you're chasing. It takes our central heroes to new places and wraps up Marvel's decade-long journey so beautifully.
critic.name: Preston Barta
publication.name: Fresh Fiction

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a fun, crafty and ultimately gratifying conclusion to one of the biggest sagas in pop culture history. A wonderful achievement. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Nicolás Ruiz
publication.name: Código espagueti

quote: When it finally fires up its big plot engine, the movie plays like a remix of Marvel's greatest hits, riffing on 40 hours of cinematic continuity and using the elastic nature of its comic-book origins as a strength.
critic.name: Norman Wilner
publication.name: NOW Toronto

quote: This is, despite its faults and three-hour running time, a fine end to a cinematic series that's become a bona fide cultural phenomenon.
critic.name: David 'Mad Dog' Bradley
publication.name: Adelaide Review

quote: For young adults who have literally grown up with these movies, the experience may be emotionally overwhelming.
critic.name: Jake Wilson
publication.name: The Age (Australia)

quote: There's a frantic busyness to the whole thing that wearied me but may well delight Marvel nuts.
critic.name: Paul Whitington
publication.name: Irish Independent

quote: It's nice to see how unafraid the film is being a finale; Endgame makes the franchise's history, and legacy, part of its story. The MCU will continue after this, but its current era feels finished in a fitting way.
critic.name: Brandon Zachary
publication.name: CBR

quote: Avengers: Endgame feels simply massive. In scale. In scope. In story. In cast list.
critic.name: Matt Oakes
publication.name: Silver Screen Riot

quote: The film may be slightly overstuffed, but the movie uses its epic runtime to keep its numerous characters not only busy, but done justice, occasionally even in ways that will surprise you.
critic.name: Andrea Thompson
publication.name: A Reel of One's Own

quote: Every single action sequence here deserves to be seen on the largest screen possible.
critic.name: Mike Sorrentino
publication.name: CNET

quote: When the action ends, the conclusion that follows is drawn-out and bland.
critic.name: Tony Macklin
publication.name: tonymacklin.net

quote: The Motion Picture Academy never recognizes great acting if it comes attached to a costume or a cape. That doesn't mean Downey isn't deserving of an Oscar. It's great acting in a great film.
critic.name: Richard Roeper
publication.name: Chicago Sun-Times

quote: These heroes will surely have other adventures, but this is the first time the MCU has taken a breath and lived in a moment. I hope its success will embolden Marvel to do this more often.
critic.name: Fred Topel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: Avengers: Endgame gifts many of the most intense and moving sequences of the franchise. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Diego Batlle
publication.name: La Nación (Argentina)

quote: A film that is equal parts grand finale and promises more of the same with a different coat of paint. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Benjamín Harguindey
publication.name: EscribiendoCine

quote: The monumental feats of the film make the imperfections seem minimal. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Juanma Fernández París
publication.name: El Nuevo Día (Puerto Rico)

quote: A terrific conclusion to this particular chapter of the MCU and one that gives fans everything they want and deserve from an epic superhero offering. (Full Content Review for Parents - Violence, Profanity, etc. - also Available)
critic.name: Jim Judy
publication.name: Screen It!

quote: [I]t is slick and affectionate enough for its three-hour running time to pass quickly.
critic.name: Nicholas Barber
publication.name: BBC.com

quote: "Endgame" is a satisfying swansong, nothing short of a fitting heroes' end. Thanks, Marvel.
critic.name: Dana Barbuto
publication.name: The Patriot Ledger

quote: Which is to say, if you think you need to see "Avengers: Endgame," you absolutely, positively need to see "Avengers: Endgame."
critic.name: Joe Gross
publication.name: Austin American-Statesman

quote: The MCU sticks this landing, allowing us to let go of years of baggage and get ready for the next flight.
critic.name: John Wenzel
publication.name: Denver Post

quote: I won't go so far as to say it's a perfect film, but still quite mind-blowing that it's able to pull together such a fun, satisfying close.
critic.name: Kyle Wilson
publication.name: The Lamplight Review

quote: All in all, it is a wonderfully exhilarating conclusion to the saga.
critic.name: Brian Viner
publication.name: Daily Mail (UK)

quote: It's an entertainment designed to please many, many people and disappoint as few as possible, extravagant without necessarily having a vision beyond its desire not to put a foot wrong.
critic.name: Stephanie Zacharek
publication.name: TIME Magazine

quote: Perhaps the Russos have made the final installment of the series this lackluster to make it easier to say goodbye to the superheroes, in this iteration. We really don't need another one. Not like this.
critic.name: Katie Walsh
publication.name: Tribune News Service

quote: Style and content almost perfectly coalesce in Endgame, combining a well-structured narrative and rich characterisation with grand set pieces.
critic.name: Jack King
publication.name: One Room With A View

quote: Endgame asks, "What does it mean to be a hero and to feel heroic? Can you get up again, and what does that look like?" These big questions are answered, I'd argue, lovingly in this film.
critic.name: Karen Gordon
publication.name: Original Cin

quote: Earth's Mightiest Heroes get the send off they richly deserve, but with one considerable caveat.
critic.name: Christian Toto
publication.name: HollywoodInToto.com

quote: This film's heart, though, belongs to Scarlett Johansson, whose sadness perhaps best articulates just what has been lost. ..Johansson's evolution of the character has imbued her with soulful drive and compassion.
critic.name: Laura Clifford
publication.name: Reeling Reviews

quote: It offers an ending to nearly everything that has come before. That it accomplishes its goal in exciting, affecting, and mostly satisfying fashion is no small feat.
critic.name: Rob Hunter
publication.name: Film School Rejects

quote: Endgame is an incredible achievement, a bravura piece of filmmaking and a love letter to the MCU, one that still makes time to add in a couple of taco gags and some killer quips.
critic.name: Rosie Fletcher and Richard Jordan
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: Affirmation of Marvel's storytelling strategy of connecting films in a shared universe, but maybe more significantly, it's proof that the franchise's consistent release schedule gives the viewer better short-term recall and deeper emotional investment.
critic.name: Eric Melin
publication.name: Scene-Stealers.com

quote: It's not literature like Lord of the Rings, but in its own way, it's pretty damn impactful.
critic.name: Jeremy Jahns
publication.name: JeremyJahns.com

quote: Avengers: Endgame is mostly adequate, if overlong, but if it had spent a little more time on imagination over spectacle, it might have had a chance of being the kind of overwhelming cinematic epoch that it is clearly aiming to be.
critic.name: Peter Sobczynski
publication.name: eFilmCritic.com

quote: Endgame is the participation trophy you get after committing 11 years to these characters.
critic.name: Radheyan Simonpillai
publication.name: CTV's Your Morning

quote: The scale, emotional weight, visual spectacle, complexity, and power of Avengers: Endgame exceeds everything fans could hope for.
critic.name: Mark Hughes
publication.name: Forbes

quote: With a plot that spans the universe, a huge cast and a three-hour run time, the movie could easily feel bloated. But directors Joe and Anthony Russo skillfully keep the action nimble...
critic.name: Julie Washington
