publication.name: Cleveland Plain Dealer

quote: It was designed to cap a decade of buildup around a single gigantic story... In that sense, it's certainly a triumph: it's ambitious, towering, and above all, daring in its difference.
critic.name: Tasha Robinson
publication.name: The Verge

quote: It isn't just as good as I was hoping it would be. It's actually better than I could have imagined. Bravo.
critic.name: Graeme Tuckett
publication.name: Stuff.co.nz

quote: Although it verges on fan-service and self-service, the film's central hour earns both because the balance of comedy, drama and action to playful invention and careful characterisation holds so sure.
critic.name: Kevin Harley
publication.name: The List

quote: This is a movie that dazzles you with its spectacle, provides plenty of irreverent slapstick and gags along the way and yet still ends with a huge emotional kick.
critic.name: Geoffrey Macnab
publication.name: Independent (UK)

quote: This three-hour epic is more or less what we were all looking for. Regardless of whether the Avengers saga goes on, this one satisfyingly closes the book on its first era, eleven years that remade the movies.
critic.name: Kyle Smith
publication.name: National Review

quote: No other movie franchise has created this sort of suspense in one film and resolved it so spectacularly in the next.
critic.name: Kristian M. Lin
publication.name: Fort Worth Weekly

quote: The movie is ludicrously long, clocking in at three hours and one minute, but surprisingly satisfying.
critic.name: Mark Feeney
publication.name: Boston Globe

quote: ...while End Game is a crowd-pleaser through and through, what wasn't expected was for this last chapter to pack such an emotional wallop.
critic.name: Tom Santilli
publication.name: Movie Show Plus

quote: Succeeds at its daunting task: summing up an epic struggle with bedazzling action... and with more humor, zest and feeling -- the real, heartfelt stuff -- than you'd dare to expect from what is, after all, an immense industrial undertaking.
critic.name: Joe Morgenstern
publication.name: Wall Street Journal

quote: A grandiloquent spectacle that passes by in what feels like seconds.
critic.name: Alistair Harkness
publication.name: Scotsman

quote: Fan service can be satisfying, just not the way the writers and directors handle it here, so by the time they get back to moments of gravitas, it is already too late.
critic.name: Alan Zilberman
publication.name: Washington City Paper

quote: In the end, the focus is on the heart of the team that started it all. Tears will be shed. I may have felt something welling up myself.
critic.name: Eli Glasner
publication.name: CBC News

quote: This cap to a villain arc that began in Thor (2011) features the most gloriously fluid and beautifully-paced action sequences this reviewer has seen in a superhero film, but marred by a distractingly high number of convenient plot contrivances...
critic.name: John Lui
publication.name: The Straits Times (Singapore)

quote: Endgame offers a rich assemblage of movement and detail, full of winning digressions and loyalty-rewarding callbacks.
critic.name: Richard Lawson
publication.name: Vanity Fair

quote: This is a solid adventure that fans will go nuts for.
critic.name: Sara Michelle Fetters
publication.name: MovieFreak.com

quote: Not only pays off in nearly every conceivable respect, but frequently surpasses one's loftiest hopes. For casual fans, it's the can't-miss event of the season. For die-hards, it earns its spot as the can't-miss event of the decade.
critic.name: Dustin Putman
publication.name: TheFilmFile.com

quote: Endgame is a movie that is nothing you'd expect but everything you want.
critic.name: Brandon Katz
publication.name: Observer

quote: A remarkable conclusion to one of the greatest sagas in the history of cinema. Avengers: Endgame is (pun intended) truly marvelous
critic.name: Vladimir Jean-Gilles
publication.name: Shifter Magazine

quote: For a movie with a daunting three-hour running time, Endgame impresses with how it continually maintains a breathtaking storytelling pace that guarantees boredom is never an option.
critic.name: Leigh Paatsch
publication.name: Herald Sun (Australia)

quote: The Russo brothers effectively dose the action throughout demonstrating a robust confidence behind the camera. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Alberto Corona
publication.name: Sensacine

quote: An earnest, overstuffed, fitfully funny superhero melodrama, Endgame hits the buttons it wants to hit, and sometimes affectingly.
critic.name: A.A. Dowd
publication.name: AV Club

quote: Big budget action filmmaking doesn't get much better than this.
critic.name: J.R. Kinnard
publication.name: PopMatters

quote: "Endgame" contemplates big-picture themes within a superhero framework and delivers a hugely entertaining ride worthy of its monumental buildup.
critic.name: Adam Graham
publication.name: Detroit News

quote: In a sense, "Endgame" is an example of the MCU cannibalizing itself, but it has always done so. And it does so here in a fresh way that is closer to homage than lazy appropriation.
critic.name: Michael O'Sullivan
publication.name: Washington Post

quote: A completely satisfying conclusion...with a deep understanding of the characters and a truly remarkable ability to find a nuanced balance between canon and innovation.
critic.name: Nell Minow
publication.name: Movie Mom

quote: Avengers:Endgame, as a slice of entertainment, may offer an emotional goodbye to some beloved characters. But as a slice of idealism, it offers a call to start living up to what we love about them.
critic.name: Roe McDermott
publication.name: Hot Press

quote: The franchise has its ups and downs; the first "Avengers" film is certainly a highlight. But the sequels have the wisecracking-superteam formula on lockdown. They always deliver everything fans could hope for - except maybe any genuine surprise.
critic.name: Kerry Lengel
publication.name: Arizona Republic

quote: Avengers: Endgame teaches us in three hours... to cling to the faintest light at the end of the tunnel, fight for it and be willing to sacrifice even for the common good. [Full review in Spanish]
critic.name: Ruben Peralta Rigaud
publication.name: Cocalecas

quote: This movie, without the emotional and historical build up that the myriad of Marvel films brought before it, would simply be a better directed Justice League.
critic.name: Matthew Razak
publication.name: Flixist.com

quote: ...this movie is mostly about bringing this phase of the Marvel universe to a spectacular and moving close, and the Russo brothers do it brilliantly.
critic.name: Jo Berry
publication.name: Movies4Kids

quote: I laughed, cried, gasped and felt the hairs on my arm stand up as I marvelled at how brilliantly a 22-film arc was brought to a close with Avengers: Endgame.
critic.name: Sinead Brennan
publication.name: RTÉ (Ireland)

quote: Endgame often pays tribute to itself, which makes it as fascinating as it is self-serious. It taps into a live wire of doomy tragedy and phoenix-like rebirth that comics do so well.
critic.name: Joshua Rothkopf
publication.name: Time Out

quote: Avengers: Endgame is both the end of an era and the beginning of a new one; a briefly closed door; a definitive end, but with a caveat.
critic.name: Joel Harley
publication.name: Starburst

quote: With clear stakes, a dialed-in cast, and the means to bring so much spectacle to life, Avengers: Endgame is quite the achievement.
critic.name: Aaron Neuwirth
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: Endgame reinforces that there's still a beating heart beneath all the machinery.
critic.name: Esther Zuckerman
publication.name: Thrillist

quote: In terms of sheer entertainment value, it's on the higher end of the MCU, a film that elevates its most iconic heroes to the legendary status they deserve and provides a few legitimate thrills along the way.
critic.name: Brian Tallerico
publication.name: RogerEbert.com

quote: A potent reminder of all that's good and bad about movies.
critic.name: Hannah Strong
publication.name: Little White Lies

quote: It's a worthy bookend to an ambitious cycle of interlocking blockbusters, credible fan service, and far and away the best film to have Avengers in the title.
critic.name: Andrew Parker
publication.name: The Gate

quote: What "The Deathly Hallows" was to "Harry Potter," what "Return of the Jedi" was to the original "Star Wars," this gargantuan "Endgame" will be to the "Avengers."
critic.name: Rafer Guzman
publication.name: Newsday

quote: The japey inter-hero rivalries and beyond-state-of-the-art visuals go down as easily as always in a formula which, if never quite revolutionising the comic book saga, gave it a much-needed overhaul...
critic.name: Danny Leigh
publication.name: Financial Times

quote: Takes the MCU, 21 films worth of scrapes, near misses and heroic feats, and unleashes a magnificent mortality fable.
critic.name: Cameron Williams
publication.name: The Popcorn Junkie

quote: There's more high drama at work in this team-up feature than anything in the series. But the soft and tender moments work best.
critic.name: Jonathan W. Hickman
publication.name: Daily Film Fix

quote: Endgame is not as tightly woven in its tapestry of tone as Infinity War and sometimes finds itself stuck between victory lap and valediction. A champagne problem, but it's one to which the Marvel honchos have found a thrilling solution.
critic.name: Nick Rogers
publication.name: Midwest Film Journal

quote: Mathematicians say infinity has no end. Avengers: Endgame thrillingly and movingly proves them wrong.
critic.name: Peter Howell
publication.name: Toronto Star

quote: "Avengers: Endgame is the most satisfying film I've ever seen. It's satisfying in a way that no other film could match because of a history that goes back over a decade."
critic.name: Jenna Busch
publication.name: Legion of Leia at Vital Thrills

quote: Marvel tourists may surprise themselves how much they care...while fanatics will have a geekgasm of heretofore undiscovered proportions at what amounts to the biggest series finale ever. To put it more politely, they'll love it "times 3000."
critic.name: Peter Canavese
publication.name: Groucho Reviews

quote: Endgame orchestrates defeat, hope, struggle, courage, triumph, and denouement in perfect balance... as all things should be.
critic.name: Kevin A. Ranson
publication.name: MovieCrypt.com

quote: Despite a slower first act, once it warms up, Endgame is everything fans would want from the climax of this epic, decade-long journey.
critic.name: Joe Passmore
publication.name: Attitude

quote: If you've survived all the cliffhangers Marvel has tossed about in its awesome masterplan; pray tell, what happens after the dust has settled? It's epic. Quite somber, but epic.
critic.name: Elias Savada
publication.name: Film International

quote: Oh yes indeed. "Avengers: Endgame" brought it.
critic.name: Moira MacDonald
publication.name: Seattle Times

quote: Even at three-plus hours, the gargantuan Avengers: Endgame is light on its feet and more freely inventive than it needed to be.
critic.name: David Edelstein
publication.name: New York Magazine/Vulture

quote: Endgame mostly sticks the landing with a satisfying conclusion, providing a final act to the Marvel Cinematic Universe that emotionally resonates in surprising ways.
critic.name: Michelle Jaworski
publication.name: The Daily Dot

quote: Plainly stated: Avengers: Endgame is the payoff for all the time, and inspiration, and joy you've invested in the MCU all these years-and it pays well
critic.name: Sherin Nicole
publication.name: idobi.com

quote: In fact, give Marvel props for not splitting it into two separate blockbusters that would have diluted the impact of such an apt, respectful and yes, emotional capper to the saga.
critic.name: Hope Madden
publication.name: Columbus Underground

quote: (No spoilers) The Return Of The King of superhero movies. An epic end chapter that closes a legacy in the best way, living up to the lofty expectations.
critic.name: Matt Neal
publication.name: ABC Radio (Australia)

quote: If this film doesn't win an Oscar for Best Picture, no superhero film should.
critic.name: Catalina Combs
publication.name: Black Girl Nerds

quote: True to its title, Avengers: Endgame delivers a first for the Marvel Cinematic Universe: an ending.
critic.name: Simon Miraudo
publication.name: Student Edge

quote: Like the Phoenix rising from the ashes, the Russo brothers switch from defense to offense for a satisfying conclusion to the series worthy of respect from Marvel fans.
critic.name: Joe Friar
publication.name: The Victoria Advocate

quote: A truly satisfying and at times surprising watch, Endgame will leave you full of sadness, but also hope for what's to come.
critic.name: Joseph Walsh
publication.name: The Skinny

quote: What can I say but "Thanks Marvel", and "Excelsior!"
critic.name: Min-sik Yoon
publication.name: Korea Herald

quote: Despite some flaws, there's no denying that this is a truly impressive achievement and a worthy conclusion to a story years in the making.
critic.name: Hugh Armitage
publication.name: Digital Spy

quote: Every dazzling, thrilling moment nurtures the narrative, celebrates the characters, and cradles the entire saga carefully towards a beautiful finish.
critic.name: James Marsh
publication.name: South China Morning Post

quote: An emotionally affecting three-hour spectacle, 'Avengers: Endgame' is the rousing and exhilarating conclusion fans deserve.
critic.name: Doug Jamieson
publication.name: The Jam Report

quote: If you think you know where this movie is going based off of the over-abundance of teasers and trailers, I assure you, you don't.
critic.name: Kirsten Acuna
publication.name: Insider

quote: All of the prodigious forethought and fortitude has paid off.
critic.name: Don Shanahan
publication.name: Every Movie Has a Lesson

quote: For a movie with such a compelling premise and a humongous build-up, it would be a shame if the payoff is weak. Thankfully that's not the case here, and for that I'm grateful.
critic.name: Ruth Maramis
publication.name: FlixChatter Film Blog

quote: Avengers: Endgame is not just a remarkable movie; it's an unforgettable experience.
critic.name: Chase Whale
publication.name: ChaseWhale.com

quote: As I type through the tears, I can wholeheartedly report that the Marvel Cinematic Universe does not disappoint and providing fans with an endgame not soon to be forgotten. Kudos Russo Brothers and Marvel. Y'all did the damn thing!!!
critic.name: Carla Renata
publication.name: The Curvy Film Critic

quote: As a continuation of the risk-taking Thanos saga, the feature isn't quite as daring as expected.
critic.name: Brian Orndorf
publication.name: Blu-ray.com

quote: This induces gasps, giggles and goosebumps a' plenty.
critic.name: Courtney Howard
publication.name: Fresh Fiction

quote: With an experimental narrative for its genre, Avengers: Endgame may have its faults, but it'll surely keep the super fans satisfied, and those who may not be so interested on their toes.
critic.name: Luke Parker
publication.name: We Got This Covered

quote: A satisfying and emotionally involving conclusion to an epic saga of beloved superheroes. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Rene Sanchez
publication.name: Cine Sin Fronteras

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a staggering, sweeping epic that touches every corner of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. You could watch the film a dozen times and discover something new.
critic.name: Julian Roman
publication.name: MovieWeb

quote: If AVENGERS: INFINITY WAR was a treatise on the Freshman year PoliSci theories of the intergalactic evil-monger, Thanos, then its follow-up is an epic poem on the cosmic futility of the Marvel Cinematic Universe.
critic.name: Rubin Safaya
publication.name: Cinemalogue

quote: Millions of us have invested countless hours and billions of dollars in these MCU movies so the outcome holds cosmic consequence.The payoff here is considerable and a worthy conclusion to this enormous part of the franchise.
critic.name: Linda and Al Lerner
publication.name: Movies and Shakers

quote: ...a delicious platter of delights designed specifically for the fans, that only very occasionally begins to feel like fan service.
critic.name: Anthony O'Connor
publication.name: FILMINK (Australia)

quote: I came out of this movie completely blown away. I think it is way better than 'Infinity War'
critic.name: Rachel Wagner
publication.name: Rachel's Reviews (YouTube)

quote: It's jamming a decade of movies, 22 films in all, and balling them up into a densely packed three-hour movie and hurling it right at your face. Some will welcome the projectile and others will recoil in horror.
critic.name: Sean Mulvihill
publication.name: FanboyNation.com

quote: A little slow getting to the meat of the plot but still has that pizzazz of being in the MCU where they blend emotions, battles and very definitely humor.
critic.name: Jackie K. Cooper
publication.name: jackiekcooper.com

quote: "Avengers: Endgame" feels more like a Christopher Nolan movie than one stemming from the MCU. It's also, by far, the best 'Avengers' movie of the four released.
critic.name: Jordan Ruimy
publication.name: World of Reel

quote: Despite the first 2 hours being a mix of pros and cons, the final hour is perhaps the greatest hour in the history of the genre, making Endgame a truly satisfying conclusion to the 22 film arc.
critic.name: John Campea
publication.name: The John Campea Show

quote: A spectacle that is genuinely affecting and packed with properly exciting moments that will literally make you draw your breath, clap and whoop, and jump out of your seat
critic.name: Wenlei Ma
publication.name: News.com.au

quote: For much of the experience, Endgame feels like you're reading a really good graphic novel.
critic.name: Kyle Pinion
publication.name: The Beat

quote: "It's a satisfying culmination of all of the films."
critic.name: Scott Chitwood
publication.name: ComingSoon.net

quote: Fan theories that have peppered the internet in the last year prove to be more exciting and interesting than the actual movie.
critic.name: Louisa Moore
publication.name: Screen Zealots

quote: ... A spectacle and feat of storytelling unlike anything the movies have ever seen.
critic.name: Greg Maki
publication.name: Star-Democrat (Easton, MD)

quote: After more than a decade and nearly two dozen pictures, the first era of the MCU comes to an imperfect, crowd-pleasing end with "Avengers: Endgame," a bulky film tasked with resolving myriad plot points and perhaps even more emotional through-lines.
critic.name: Tim Grierson
publication.name: Screen International

quote: Endgame certainly showed there was one and it was just what we needed.
critic.name: Kristen Lopez
publication.name: Culturess

quote: "Endgame" is the most emotional of the Avengers movies, a tear-stained farewell that effectively tugs at the heartstrings while simultaneously blowing them up with a large army's worth of CGI warfare.
critic.name: Cary Darling
publication.name: Houston Chronicle

quote: It's a quality action movie that accomplishes, with seeming ease, a number of difficult things.
critic.name: Mick LaSalle
publication.name: San Francisco Chronicle

quote: It fulfills everything that was set up in "Infinity War."
critic.name: Jason Guerrasio
publication.name: Business Insider

quote: If you have anything close to the bond with these characters as the filmmakers hope you do, you'll be satisfied. You'll laugh. You'll cry. You'll shout "yeah!" and clap.
critic.name: Kyle Anderson
publication.name: Nerdist

quote: A fitting capper to one of the biggest franchises of all time.
critic.name: Chris Bumbray
publication.name: JoBlo's Movie Network

quote: The most confusing and convoluted of any of the Marvel Cinematic Universe films, yet it's also unbelievably satisfying.
critic.name: Mike Ryan
publication.name: Uproxx

quote: Surprisingly smaller-scale and lighter than INFINITY WAR, with disappointing action to boot, but it ends on a high note and the key characters get pushed in interesting directions.
critic.name: Scott Mendelson
publication.name: Forbes

quote: A sometimes ponderous and always-pandering script gets by on the considerable charm of that wonderful cast, one last time.
critic.name: Roger Moore
publication.name: Movie Nation

quote: Avengers Endgame is a beautiful and satisfying culmination of 22 films in the MCU. This film is not only monumental but a love letter to earth's mightiest heroes and its fans.
critic.name: Sharronda Williams
publication.name: Pay or Wait

quote: This is blockbuster filmmaking of the highest order. Avengers: Endgame is the culmination of a decade's worth of stories, character growth, and audience investment.
critic.name: Victor Stiff
publication.name: That Shelf

quote: As it unfolds, the film invites you to forget about whatever you came in deciding it would be.
critic.name: Dominick Suzanne-Mayer
publication.name: Consequence

quote: The most impressive aspect of what's sure to be one of the biggest blockbusters in history is how intimate and personal so much of the story is and how quieter character moments aren't lost in the shuffle.
critic.name: Rebecca Murray
publication.name: Showbiz Junkies

quote: "Speeches are given, battles are fought, jokes are thrown-many of them. In fact, they pack a LOT of funny into this three hours, for good or ill. In the end, the satisfaction of having stayed the course with Marvel is rewardedtenfold."
critic.name: Khal Davenport
publication.name: Complex

quote: Directors Anthony and Joe Russo have somehow crafted a coherent and exhilarating epic that incorporates all your favorite superheroes (and many of their loved ones) in one emotionally resonant package.
critic.name: Mara Reinstein
publication.name: Us Weekly

quote: Marvel has built up an incredible amount of emotional currency and Endgame is a very satisfying payoff
critic.name: Travis Hopson
publication.name: Punch Drunk Critics

quote: Every serious narrative beat in the film is ultimately undercut by pro-forma storytelling, or by faux-improvised humor.
critic.name: Keith Uhlich
publication.name: Slant Magazine

quote: Delivers on all fronts with the most satisfying final acts I've ever seen. This was like a Thanos snap to my expectations and then some.
critic.name: Jeffrey Lyles
publication.name: Lyles' Movie Files

quote: One word comes to mind, and it's a word that has never been associated with just about anything regarding the whole of the Marvel Cinematic Universe; finality
critic.name: Robert Kojder
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: [Joe and Anthony Russo] take every cent of capital that these movies have earned over the last 11 years & spend it in the best, most economic way you could possibly imagine.
critic.name: Dan Murrell
publication.name: Screen Junkies

quote: I can't recall a film in this cinematic universe or any other that works as relentlessly and ingeniously to keep delighting its audience than this.
critic.name: Robbie Collin
publication.name: Daily Telegraph (UK)

quote: Downright Spielberg-ian! A perfect way to cap off ten years of the MCU, and get audiences excited for the next ten.
critic.name: Grace Randolph
publication.name: Beyond the Trailer

quote: A victory lap that moonwalks through the best part of the MCU back catalogue and emphasises emotion as much as action, this is an intensely satisfying piece of blockbuster filmmaking.
critic.name: Helen O'Hara
publication.name: Empire Magazine

quote: The movie works because it delivers everything you want and all the things you didn't know you needed.
critic.name: Spencer Perry
publication.name: ComingSoon.net

quote: If you've invested years of your life to the MCU [Marvel Cinematic Universe] like I have, this movie will feel like a fan letter to you. Kevin Feige and his team deserve so much praise for being able to pull off something of this magnitude.
critic.name: Dorian Parks
publication.name: Geeks of Color

quote: [O]ne of the most ambitious, entertaining, emotional, and stunning blockbusters we've ever seen, and the best film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe canon thus far.
critic.name: Eric Eisenberg
publication.name: CinemaBlend

quote: We haven't seen anything like this before in franchise movie-making. One can only hope that the next 10 years of Marvel storytelling comes close to this.
critic.name: Mark Daniell
publication.name: Toronto Sun

quote: This decade with the costumed adventurers has been worth it. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: Yago García
publication.name: Cinemanía (Spain)

quote: As "Endgame" sputters to the finish line, it leaves the impression of witnessing a Marvel Movie Marathon compressed to three hours - and 58 seconds, but trust me, they're disposable - of unbridled fan service.
critic.name: Eric Kohn
publication.name: indieWire

quote: Spectacle gives way to heroic journeys fulfilled, quests finally culminating and closure finally reached.
critic.name: Jason Gorber
publication.name: HighDef Digest

quote: Rarely do event movies live up to the hype, but Avengers: Endgame shatters any expectations. A glorious superhero epic!
critic.name: EJ Moreno
publication.name: Flickering Myth

quote: It's everything a fan could want.
critic.name: Nick Johnston
publication.name: Vanyaland

quote: An undeniable triumph for Marvel and an essential appointment for fans of the genre. [Full Review in Spanish]
critic.name: John Tones
publication.name: Espinof

quote: If Avengers Endgame -- with its carefully crafted emotional beats, thrilling action sequences and heartbreaking farewells to some of our most beloved heroes -- isn't the perfect final chapter, I can't imagine what perfection might look like.
critic.name: Brent Hankins
publication.name: The Lamplight Review

quote: "Avengers: Endgame" delivers everything Marvel fans will enjoy and not much that they expect.
critic.name: Sean P. Means
publication.name: Salt Lake Tribune

quote: More than any of those franchises, "Endgame," at its best moments, carries the thrill of classic comic-book twists and reversals.
critic.name: Jake Coyle
publication.name: Associated Press

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a satisfying finale to the Marvel Cinematic Universe chapters we've watched and loved. This one may not be for small children, though, due to language and violence.
critic.name: Tania Lamb
publication.name: Lola Lambchops

quote: Endgame is truly a masterful piece of storytelling, which both goes exactly where you expect it to, and not at all.
critic.name: Anne Cohen
publication.name: Refinery29

quote: Part of the journey is the end, and this goes out with a bang that'll make you whimper.
critic.name: Jamie Graham
publication.name: Total Film

quote: A massive, incredibly entertaining epic that is as emotional as it is spectacular.
critic.name: Don Kaye
publication.name: Den of Geek

quote: The most shocking thing about Avengers: Endgame is that there are several moments within this colossal movie that feel like a Marvel miracle.
critic.name: Alex Abad-Santos
publication.name: Vox

quote: Endgame knows what its audience wants, and delivers that without feeling like quote-unquote fan service.
critic.name: Susana Polo
publication.name: Polygon

quote: [T]he entire endeavour loses any sense of emotional stakes or general meaning beyond the deliverance of crass fan-service and incomprehensible visuals.
critic.name: Barry Hertz
publication.name: Globe and Mail

quote: Avengers: Endgame wraps up the story of the MCU so far, delivering an epic superhero adventure while honoring the past in a satisfying finale.
critic.name: Molly Freeman
publication.name: Screen Rant

quote: If the Marvel superhero movies on the whole are your favorite band's individual albums, "Avengers: Endgame" is the triple-disc greatest-hits package with the really awesome cover and a slew of familiar, comforting gems inside.
critic.name: Brian Truitt
publication.name: USA Today

quote: I wasn't sure, after the tedium of Infinity War, that Marvel could wrap this up in a satisfying way. Turns out, it was a snap.
critic.name: Gary Thompson
publication.name: Philadelphia Daily News

quote: The longer run-time and bloated cast are surprising strengths, permitting this grand finale to be more than just a superhero flick. A fitting, over-arching conclusion by a studio that knows how to get this genre spot on.
critic.name: J. Don Birnam
publication.name: Splash Report

quote: A fitting and surprisingly poetic payoff to more than a decade of storytelling, and the start of a bright new chapter.
critic.name: Laura Prudom
publication.name: IGN Movies

quote: This is Marvel flexing, building on over 10 years and 20-plus films of careful groundwork and intricate planning to show us what it can do that no other movie franchise can. As such, it's an immensely satisfying finish to this era of the series.
critic.name: Angie Han
publication.name: Mashable

quote: Endgame is an extremely well-made film, helmed by two directors who knew exactly what they were doing the whole time.
critic.name: Tom Fitzgerald and Lorenzo Marquez
publication.name: Tom & Lorenzo

quote: You have to hand it to the directors for their ambition in bringing together a clown car full of characters into such a well-told and compelling yarn.
critic.name: Johnny Oleksinski
publication.name: New York Post

quote: Avengers: Endgame is a lot - sometimes too much. But, wow, the payoff is huge. It leaves you proud to have invested over a decade in a franchise that delivers an inspiring exploration of what it means to be family and a hero.
critic.name: Perri Nemiroff
publication.name: Collider Video

quote: [E]xtravagant - and mostly very gratifying.
critic.name: Michael Phillips
publication.name: Chicago Tribune

quote: For now, the cast, crew, and creators of the past decade may rest easy on a sun-drench porch with the knowledge that [Endgame] accomplished their ultimate goal. For better or for worse.
critic.name: Robert Daniels
publication.name: 812filmreviews

quote: The Avengers, as a concept, probably won't be going anywhere, but Endgame still feels like a proper goodbye.
critic.name: David Sims
publication.name: The Atlantic

quote: It's game over for Marvel's competition as their latest superhero spectacular smashes into cinemas like the Hulk on steroids, and is the thunderous triumph we've all been hoping for.
critic.name: Chris Hunneysett
publication.name: Daily Mirror (UK)

quote: For the most part, Endgame delivers on the unique brand of humor, action and drama that Marvel has down to a science at this point.
critic.name: Thaddeus McCollum
publication.name: Orlando Weekly

quote: Having set up a formidable task and then some with the finish of "Infinity War," "Avengers: Endgame" rises to the challenge, delivering an epic finale that proves immensely satisfying.
critic.name: Brian Lowry
publication.name: CNN.com

quote: At its best - and "Endgame" is in some ways as good as it gets - the "Avengers" cosmos has been an expansive and inclusive place.
critic.name: A.O. Scott
publication.name: New York Times

quote: Endgame reaches a conclusion that is not only spectacularly satisfying, but thematically powerful.
critic.name: Russ Fischer
publication.name: Birth.Movies.Death.

quote: The movie largely delivers, splashing its ambitious three-hour narrative across a sprawling canvas of characters, eras, and not-quite-insurmountable challenges.
critic.name: Leah Greenblatt
publication.name: Entertainment Weekly

quote: Emotionally epic in every sense of the word, Endgame is a satisfying conclusion to the MCU's 11-year conquest that delivers enough feels and action to cream your pants over.
critic.name: Rendy Jones
publication.name: Rendy Reviews

quote: By carrying the weight of 21 movies with it, Endgame feels far grander, surprising, and emotional than your typical sequel.
critic.name: Matt Goldberg
publication.name: Collider

quote: Avengers: Endgame perfectly ties together the entire MCU. It has always been connected, but now it is complete. An emotional roller coaster I cannot wait to ride again.
critic.name: Tessa Smith
publication.name: Mama's Geeky

quote: [W]hat comes across most strongly here, oddly enough for an effects-driven comic-book-derived film, is the character acting, especially from Downey, Ruffalo, Evans, Hemsworth, Brolin and Paul Rudd as Ant-Man.
critic.name: Todd McCarthy
publication.name: Hollywood Reporter

quote: Avengers: Endgame goes galaxies beyond expectations and exceeds anything that any of us could have imagined. The perfect end to an incredible series of films.
critic.name: Scott Davis
publication.name: HeyUGuys

quote: I have to admit, in all its surreal grandiosity, in all its delirious absurdity, there is a huge sugar rush of excitement to this mighty finale, finally interchanging with euphoric emotion and allowing us to say poignant farewells.
critic.name: Peter Bradshaw
publication.name: Guardian

quote: Our heroes are giving their final bow and it is a joy and pleasure to witness.
critic.name: Ashley Menzel
publication.name: We Live Entertainment

quote: After the must-see showdown that was 'Infinity War,' the Russo brothers deliver a more fan-facing three-hour followup, rewarding loyalty to Marvel Cinematic Universe.
critic.name: Peter Debruge
publication.name: Variety

quote: Has almost nothing on its mind but crossing the Ts and dotting the Is of a far-flung superhero saga, but to anyone with even a minor emotional stake in the MCU, it has the fleeting satisfaction of a shot of whipped cream direct from the spray can.
critic.name: Alonso Duralde
publication.name: TheWrap

quote: Ultimately, Avengers: Endgame feels exhausting. That's not a knock against the movie, though.
critic.name: Chris Evangelista
publication.name: Slashfilm

quote: Avengers: Endgame is everything you've ever dreamed a Marvel movie could be. It's a three-hour adrenaline shot to the heart featuring mysteries solved, consequences suffered, shock, awe, and delight
critic.name: Germain Lussier
publication.name: io9.com

quote: Endgame is the best possible love letter to the MCU one could muster, a big, sloppy kiss to its fans and the characters that made these movies so appealing in the first place.
critic.name: Clint Worthington
publication.name: The Spool

quote: A gargantuan love letter to Marvel's equally enormous mythology.
critic.name: Matt Singer
publication.name: ScreenCrush
